('1005433', 'Mahesa Nugraha', 'An Analysis of English-Indonesian Translation Procedures on YouTube Community Guidelines', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr. Odo Fadloeli, M.A.', 'Sri Harto, M.Pd.', 'The study was aimed at finding out the most frequently translation procedures used in YouTube Community Guidelines  and analyzing whether it meet the criteria of naturalness, accuracy and clarity. This study used a descriptive qualitative research method as proposed by Creswell (2012, p. 274). The analysis of the material showed that among all of the translating procedures, transposition was the most frequently used procedure. Transposition was applied 43 times in the material. Borrowing was applied 38 times, followed by literal and modulation which had nine times applied in the material. Equivalent was applied two times. There were no adaptation and calque applied in the material.  The translation was categorized as good. The researcher uses Larson''s theory (cited in Anari and Bouali, 2009, p. 80) of good translation which is naturalness, accuracy, and clearness. \r\n\r\nKeywords: translation, tra...'),
('1005638', 'Fajar Qodariah', 'Towards Autonomous Learner in EFL Writing : Improving Students'' Writing Skill in Writing Analytical Exposition Text Through Peer Feedback', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Gin Gin Gustine, M.Pd., Ph.D.', '', 'This study intends to investigate the effectiveness of peer feedback technique in improving students'' writing skill and to examine the responses of students toward the implementation of peer feedback technique in writing analytical exposition text. It employed a mixed method design. One group pretest-posttest design was employed to gain quantitative data whereas a qualitative research design was employed by using questionnaire and interview. The data from pretest and posttest were analyzed by using a paired sample t-test in SPSS 17.0 for Windows showing that tobt was higher than tcrit (10.03>1.70) at the level of significance 0.05 indicating that the null hypothesis (H0) is rejected. It means that there was a significance difference between students'' pretest and posttest score after treatments. Moreover, the results of questionnaires and interview showed that most of the students (96.43%) gave ...'),
