('1005880', 'Galih Eka Putra', 'The Use of Cohesive Devices in English Education Students'' Writing', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Fuad Abdul Hamied, M.A., Ph.D.', 'Rd. Della Nuridah Kartika Sari A., S.Pd., M.Ed.', 'This study discovers how cohesive devices used in twelve students'' writing written by four students - two high achiever learners and two low achiever learners - of English Education Program in Indonesian University. With the characteristics of case study approach, the research study applies a qualitative method research design and employs Halliday and Hasan''s (1976) taxonomy of cohesion framework as a ground theory and a tool for text analysis. The findings show that grammatical cohesive devices are used slightly more frequent than the lexical ones. The students frequently used reiteration followed by reference, conjunction, collocation, substitution, and ellipsis with two general functions; to remind the readers about the topic discussed and to show the position of the author within the text. Furthermore, it is realized that to some extent, the way students use cohesive devices is a little bit...'),
('1006376', 'Muhammad Iqbal Nurfikri', 'An Analysis of Strategies in Translating Indonesian Cultural Words into English Subtitle of "HABIBIE & AINUN" - A FILM BY FAOZAN RIZAL', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr. Hobir Abdullah, M.Pd.', 'DRA. SRI SETYARINI, MA.,LING.', 'This study entitled "An Analysis of Strategies in Translating Indonesian Cultural Words into English Subtitle of "HABIBIE & AINUN - A FILM BY FAOZAN RIZAL." This research aims to find out the cultural words found in the "Habibi & Ainun" film and to investigate the translation strategies used by the translator in translating the cultural words in the film based on Newmark''s theory.\r\nData were collected from the transcript of Habibie & Ainun film. Qualitative descriptive is applied in this study. The collected data were analyzed through some translation strategies proposed by Newmark (1998). First, the Indonesian cultural words found in the film were categorized using Newmark''s theory. Second, the cultural words were investigated using translation strategies theory proposed by Newmark. Then analyzed the category and strategy mostly found in the film.\r\nThe findings reveal that there are 54 cultura...'),
('1100005', 'Syifa Nauval Muftia', 'The Correlation of Self-Efficacy and English Speaking Skill', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Pupung Purnawarman, M.S.Ed., Ph.D.', 'Muhammad Handi Gunawan, M.Pd.', 'This study involved sixty students of eighth grade in a junior high school in Cimahi. In this study, the data were gathered in two ways: questionnaire and speaking test. The analysis of the data was done within the theoretical frameworks of self-efficacy by Bandura (1982) and the speaking assessment criteria used to score the students'' speaking skill was the combination of IELTS and SQA (Scottish Qualification Association) speaking assessment criteria. The students'' self-efficacy score and speaking test score were computed by using Pearson Product Moment Correlation formula. The findings indicated that 5 students (8.20%) had very high self-efficacy and 13 students (21.31%) had high self-efficacy in speaking skill. Almost half of the participants (42.62%) had medium self-efficacy belief in their speaking skill. Meanwhile, there were 14 students (22.96%) who had low self-efficacy and 3 students (...'),
('1100131', 'Nyi Raden Alifa Mariani Saleha Soerianingrat', 'THE IMPLEMENTATION OF PERSONALISED LEARNING TO HELP STUDENTS IMPROVE THE LISTENING SKILL', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Nenden Sri Lengkanawati, M.Pd.', 'Muhammad Handi Gunawan, M.Pd.', 'The listening skill is a part of the English national examination (UN), and about 40% of students think that it is a hard skill to master. Thus there should be a way to help them master the skill. The aim of this study was to see if the implementation of personalised learning could help students improve their listening skill, as well as the steps of implementation and the students'' perceptions about it. About 48 freshmen were taken as the samples of this study. This quasi-experimental research was employed with a pre-test, a post-test, questionnaires and written documents as the research instruments. This study was conducted based on the five key features of personalised learning as mentioned by O''Donoghue namely 1)Ensure every learner is as active as possible; 2)Design frequent formative assessment; 3)Put the emphasis on peers learning together; 4)Consider whether learning tasks can be persona...'),
('1100185', 'Syamsul Rizal', '', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', '', '', ''),
('1100189', 'Fadhil Mochsin', 'Domestication and Foreignization Applied to Translation of Selected Quotations by a Novice Translator', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr. Odo Fadloeli, M.A.', 'Sri Harto, M.Pd.', 'This paper was aimed at finding out categories of culture-specific items in the translation of selectedquotationson LINE online dictionary translated by a novice translator and figuring out which strategy between domestication and foreignization is more dominating in translating meaning of the culture-specific items. A descriptive qualitative research method was used in this research. From 2609 quotations, there were 228 culture-specific items found. 15 Categories of CSIs  were found and 11 procedures of translation found among the categories of CSIs which 7 of them belong to domestication and 4 of them to foreignization. Strategy of foreignization was preferred in rendering cultural specific items with 64% and domestication strategy was composed of 36%. From the research, it was found that despite the dominance of foreignization strategy, the meaning of cultural specific items was not signific...'),
('1100534', 'Chika Aldila', 'THE CHARACTERISTICS OF EFFECTIVE ENGLISH TEACHERS: JUNIOR HIGH SCHOOL STUDENTS'' PERCEPTIONS (A Case Study in a Junior High School in Bandung)\r\n', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Didi Suherdi, M.Ed.', 'Iyen Nurlaelawati, M.Pd.', 'This study aims to investigate the characteristics of effective English teachers and the most important categories of the characteristics of effective English teachers based on junior high school students'' perceptions. The study is based on the theory by Brown (2000) regarding the characteristics of effective English teachers; technical knowledge, pedagogical skills, interpersonal skills, and personal qualities. The study employed case study design. Eighteen students from the ninth grade of a public junior high school in Bandung were selected as the participants of the study. Thirty item questionnaires and a semi-structured interview were used as the instruments. The findings of the study indicated that students perceived characteristics of effective English teachers such as "easy to forgive", "not easily irritated", "appreciate students'' differences", "increase students'' motivation", "friendly...'),
('1100676', 'Mohammad Reza Hafiz', 'An Investigation of Transitivity System in Junior High School Students'' Recount Texts', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Sudarsono M.I., S.Pd., M.A.', 'Iyen Nurlaelawati, M.Pd.', 'This study entitled An investigation of transitivity system in junior high school students'' recount texts aims at investigating recount texts developed by the students in terms of its schematic structures and linguistic features and revealing difficulties faced by the students in writing recount texts using transitivity system of functional linguistics developed by Halliday (1994). This study was conducted in one public school in Bandung. Six eighth grade students were selected as the participants divided into three categories; high, middle and low achievers. This study employed a descriptive qualitative case study. The findings showed that all students'' texts apply the schematic structure of recount because the texts were arranged correctly in different paragraphs. In terms of linguistic features, there were three types of processes occurring in students'' texts except on text 5 where mental pr...'),
('1101065', 'Meitha Herlina Rahman', 'IMPLEMENTING CRITICAL READING MODEL IN TEACHING READING HORTATORY TEXT (A Case Study Conducted in a Senior high School in Bandung)', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Gin Gin Gustine, M.Pd., Ph.D.', '', 'This paper aims to examine how critical reading model is implemented in teaching hortatory exposition text in English as foreign languge classroom. The subject of this study are the students of 11th grade of Linguistic Program in one senior high school in Bandung. The data obtained through classroom observation of teaching phase taking six meetings, individual interview toward randomly selected participants, distcributing questionnaire ad conducting reading model through five strategies which are previewing, identifying arguments and claims, weighing evidence, evaluating evidence and summarizing. Besides, it is also found that critical reading model is able to help students in their reading ability since the result of reading test showed that 18 out of 30 students having good score on reading test. Moreover, 83.3 5 of students think that they do not have any difficulties in learning using this ...'),
('1101069', 'Dewi Rohmatur Rokhimah', 'CONTENT EVALUATION OF ENGLISH ELECTRONIC TEXTBOOK FOR VOCATIONAL HIGH SCHOOL BASED ON BASIC COMPETENCES OF CURRICULUM 2013', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr. Wachyu Sundayana, M.A.', '', 'This study was intended to evaluate the student''s English Electronic Textbook (BSE) entitled BAHASA INGGRIS for eleven grade used in Vocational High School in Indonesia. The textbook was course book suggested by Ministry of Education and Culture to assist the implementation of Curriculum 2013. The evaluation based on basic competences on syllabus Curriculum 2013. The textbook evaluation in this study considered five criteria labelled as: (1) content; (2) vocabulary and grammar; (3) exercise and activity; (4) attractiveness of the text and physical make-up; and (5) context of the textbook in terms of material fitness with the basic competences, students and teachers need. This study used checklist evaluation through document analysis, and interview to collect data. The checklist was developed based on Miekley (2005) evaluative criteria. The study found that the textbook good developed based on b...'),
('1101100', 'Muhammad Lukman Nur Hakim', 'TRANSLATING ''MANGA'' AS A TECHNIQUE OF LEARNING ENGLISH AS A FOREIGN LANGUAGE', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr. Odo Fadloeli, M.A.', 'Sri Harto, M.Pd.', 'The challenge of language teaching in non-English spoken country is still remained to be solved. In Indonesian context, the EFL teaching has been based on the Systemic Functional Linguistic Genre Based Approach (SFL GBA) as suggested in the national curriculum (Emilia, 2011). Where, the language teaching is based on the concept of making-meaning. However, Emilia (2011) asserts that her findings from several studies in the fields show that the application in classroom interaction is troubled, misled, and miss-learned. Based on the misleading of curriculum implementation is, then, influencing learners'' cognitive (Engelmann, 1993) and affective achievement. In the cognitive aspect, the miss-learning in classroom interaction is very expensive in time, since it will need more effort to re-teaching the original concept (Engelmann, 1993).  In the affective aspect, it influences learners'' motivation an...'),
('1101701', 'Gagan Ginanjar', 'TEACHERS` EVALUATION ON THE 2013 CURRICULUM ENGLISH TEXTBOOK FOR 9th GRADE STUDENTS IN INDONESIA', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr. Wachyu Sundayana, M.A.', 'Muhammad Handi Gunawan, M.Pd.', 'The primary focus of this research is to investigate the strengths and weaknesses of English textbook for ninth grade students based on  teachers` evaluation and to find out teachers` criteria regarding good English textbook. This research is implemkenting descriptive qualitative study and phenomenology method. The data were obtanied by using two instruments; textbook evaluation and interview. The first data gained by conducting evaluation on English textbook entitled"Think Globally Act Locally" based on the evaluation instrument developed by Mukundan (2012). Since the textbook evaluated on this research is the 2013 English textbook, evaluation instrument for the 2013 curriculum textbook provided by BSNP also used as a combination. The second data gathered by implementing interview to discover teachers` opinion on criteria of good English textbook. The findings showed that the strengths of the ...'),
('1101983', 'Fadila Istiqa Septiana', 'A Priori Validity of Summative Test Items Development by EFL Teachers', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Fuad Abdul Hamied, M.A., Ph.D.', 'Rd. Della Nuridah Kartika Sari A., S.Pd., M.Ed.', 'The Ministerial Regulation Number 16 of the year 2007 on academic qualification standards and teacher competencies requires teachers to conduct an assessment and evaluation process. Therefore all teachers are supposed to be able to develop valid and reliable test for the students as validity and reliability are two important characteristics of a test. The study was designed to aim at finding out a priori validity of summative test items developed by EFL teachers in Indonesia. The method used in the data analysis is qualitative research by using Weir''s framework of a priori validity (2005). The result showed that in context validity the teachers have a problem with order of items in the task setting aspect and in task demands of writing skill. Moreover, in theory based validity the teachers have a problem in testing writing since the test format is multiple choice question.\r\nKeywords: a priori v...'),
('1102871', 'Raden Talitha Rahma Kemala', 'MULTIMEDIA TEHNOLOGY IN TEACHING ENGLISH TO YOUNG LEARNERS (A CASE STUDY AT ONE PRIVATE ENGLISH COURSE IN BANDUNG)', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Drs. Prawoto S. Purnomo, M.Pd.', 'Pupung Purnawarman, M.S.Ed., Ph.D.', 'This study is aimed to investigate the utilization of multimedia technology in teaching English to young learners. This study also describes the students'' responses and the teachers'' perception toward the use of multimedia technology in English teaching and learning activities. Participants in this study were forty young learners and three in-service teachers of EFL working at a private English course. The data were collected through classroom observations, questionnaires, and interviews. The data from the instruments were analyzed qualitatively. The result indicates that the teachers utilize the multimedia technology as a tool which helps them to (1) gain students'' attention, (2) recall prerequisites, (3) present learning objectives, (4) support learning through examples and visual elaboration, (5) elicit students'' responses, (6) provide feedback, (7) enhance retention and transfer the abstrac...'),
('1103542', 'Elina Rahmawati Halawa', 'Estimating the Relationship between Morphological Awareness and Reading Comprehension among High School Students in Bandung', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Didi Suherdi, M.Ed.', '', 'The objective of this study is to find out whether there is a significant correlation between students'' morphological awareness and their reading comprehension. Also, it intends to measure the extent to which morphological awareness predicts students'' reading comprehension. Thirty six students of X MIA 5 at SMAN 15 Bandung are selected as the samples of this research. The design used is the correlational design. The instruments used are the Test of Morphological Structure (TMS), originally designed by Joanne F Carlisle, and the Test of Reading Comprehension. Morphological awareness measures cover derivation and decomposition skill. It is calculated that there is a moderate, positive correlation between morphological awareness and reading comprehension, which is statistically significant (r = .52, n = 36, p < .001). This proves that the H0 is rejected and Ha is accepted. In addition, a simple re...'),
('1104281', 'Juwita Agustiana', 'Students'' Difficulties in Comprehending Mathematical Word Problems Written in English', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'DRA. SRI SETYARINI, MA.,LING.', 'Gin Gin Gustine, M.Pd., Ph.D.', 'This study aimed to investigate teachers'' and students'' opinions toward the difficulties of students in comprehending the mathematical word problems written in English, and investigated the strategies that the teachers used to help the students in the class. This study used a qualitative research design as the research methodology. The study was conducted in a case study design study in order to earn a good understanding about the participants'' perspective of a phenomenon. The research was conducted in one of private Mathematic course in Bandung. The writer conducted interview with the three teachers, then the questionnaire was given to three up to ten students ranging from Grades 3 to 6 of the private course. The English language learners (ELLs), as the students, were difficult to figure out the question to be answered in word problem (Bresser et al, 2008). Based on the interview, the research...'),
('1104376', 'Milda Yulia Solihah', 'An Implementation of Four Resources Model of Critical Literacy and Narrative- Cultural Analysis in Film- Based Activity', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Gin Gin Gustine, M.Pd., Ph.D.', '', 'This paper, entitled "An Implementation of Four Resources Model of Critical Literacy and Narrative-Cultural Analysis in Film-Based Activity" aims to investigate the implementation of film-based activity using critical frameworks. A film-based activity consisting of three stages: pre-viewing, while-viewing and post-viewing is developed based on Luke and Freebody''s Four Resources Model of critical literacy proposed and Bautista''s Narrative-Cultural Approach in order to achieve the purpose of this study. The activity is performed to 48 ninth-grade students by the researcher who also serves as the teacher in this practitioner research. Students are guided to write three individual responses and participate in group discussion. Some of their responses are also confirmed in focus groups interview. As a result, students show capability to become critical readers, playing the role as code breaker, mean...'),
('1104688', 'Yuli Kwania', 'The Effectiveness of Jigsaw Technique in Improving Students'' Reading Comprehension', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Drs. Prawoto S. Purnomo, M.Pd.', 'Pupung Purnawarman, M.S.Ed., Ph.D.', 'This research investigated the senior high school students'' reading comprehension improvement by implementing Jigsaw technique in teaching reading and students'' responses toward it. The design of this study is quasi experimental design which used treatment group and control group. This study used mixed method in order to obtain both quantitative data by using pre-test and post-test and qualitative data by using questionnaire. The result revealed that Jigsaw technique improved students reading comprehension and the students showed good response toward the implementation of Jigsaw technique. This quantitative finding was proved by t-test and the qualitative finding was revealed by interpreting questionnaire descriptively. Based on this research, the implementation of Jigsaw technique in teaching reading has positive effects in both students'' reading comprehension and students'' response. \r\nKeyword...'),
('1104707', 'Lidya Annisa Humaira', 'AN ANALYSIS OF ENGLISH-INDONESIAN TRANSLATING PROCEDURES OF THE MOVIE ENTITLED "BIG HERO 6" BY THREE FREELANCE TRANSLATORS', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr. Odo Fadloeli, M.A.', 'Sri Harto, M.Pd.', 'This research aims to find out the translating procedures that three freelance translators used and analyzing the quality of the translations. This research uses qualitative descriptive method. The result revealed the translating procedures used in the PA''s translation proposed by Newmark (1988, page 81) weretransposition (28 times), literal translation (18 times), naturalization and paraphrase (15 times), reduction (10 times), transference (9 times), and expansion (5 times). Meanwhile, in GD''s translation, the usage are transposition (28 times), literal translation (18 times), naturalization (12 times), transference (11 times), reduction (10 times), paraphrase (8 times), and expansion (5 times). Beside, in LG''s translation, the usage are transposition (35 times), literal translation (16 times), transference (14 times), naturalization (13 times), reduction (9 times), expansion and paraphrase (5...'),
('1104741', 'Helmi Hindasah', 'TEACHER''S TREATMENT OF GENDER ISSUES PRESENTED IN TEXTBOOK TEXTS', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Didi Suherdi, M.Ed.', 'Nicke Yunita Moecharam. S.Pd., M.A.', 'Most research under the topic of gender and foreign language textbooks have been focused solely on texts while the exploration of teacher''s treatment of it which cannot be predicted. It is aimed at investigating the ways in which the teacher treats gender issues presented in the textbook texts as learning materials and explored the topic of gender in relation to classroom interaction. It utilizes qualitative descriptive case study focusing on lessons in which the textbook presented some aspects of gender. The data shows that the texts used are considered as texts which maintain traditional representation of gender roles where the teacher mostly endorses the idea. It also revealed that the teacher ignores the discussion of possible gender issues and his treatment was somewhat unclear. From a FPDA perspective, competing discourses of gender differentiation and collaborative talk, actually work th...'),
('1104789', 'Sonia Destrie Pratidina', 'The Implementation of Peer Assessment as A Method in Assessing Students'' Descriptive Text', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Didi Suherdi, M.Ed.', 'Muhammad Handi Gunawan, M.Pd.', 'This research paper is aimed to see how peer assessment is implemented as a method in assessing students'' descriptive text and to reveal the students'' perceptions towards the implementation of peer assessment as a method in assessing students'' descriptive text. A qualitative method equipped with descriptive analysis was employed with three instruments to collect and identify the data, namely classroom observation, interviews, and questionnaire. The respondents were tenth grade students at one senior high school in Cimahi. The results reveal that the teacher has implemented peer assessment progressively through several phases; pre-implementation and implementation phase as Falchikov (2005) proposed. Furthermore, the students also reveal their positive perceptions towards the implementation of peer assessment in classroom since peer assessment offers some beneficial values for them. \r\nKeywords: a...'),
('1105126', 'Ahmad Zulkarnain', 'The Implementation of Genre-Based Approach to Teaching Writing Descriptive Text (An Action Research in Eighth Grade Students in a Junior High School in Cimahi)', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Didi Suherdi, M.Ed.', '', 'This action research carried out in two cycles purposes to investigate the ability of Genre-Based Approach in improving students? ability of writing descriptive texts and also to explore the students? attitudes towards GBA implementation. The data were collected through classroom observations, students? texts samples and a semi-structured interview employed during and after data collection. The findings prove that GBA can help improve students? ability in writing descriptive texts as reflected in students? writing achievement. They also indicate the students? positive attitude towards GBA implementation reflected in interviewees? positive responses after GBA implementation supported by classroom observations findings showing students? active involvement. Thus, it is recommended that further study of the GBA should be conducted in various contexts and levels to examine the effectiveness of this ...'),
('1105321', 'Anti Gantini', 'Classroom Management Challenges for the Pre-Service Teacher in Teaching English Speaking', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Didi Suherdi, M.Ed.', '', 'This study is aimed to investigate classroom management challenges in teaching English speaking that faced by the pre-service teacher. This was a descriptive case study using qualitative method as an approach. Classroom observations and interviews were conducted with pre-service teacher to seek his responses relating to the challenges that he faced, and the strategies he gave for improvement of classroom management. The results indicated that pre-service teacher faced six challenges in managing classroom in teaching English speaking. It was also found pre-service teacher''s strategies to overcome those challenges. The challenges were from students'' low participation, students'' speaking English skill, disrespectful attitude towards pre-service teacher, the limited amount of time and students motivation and expectation. The strategies used by pre-service teachersto overcome those challenges are ma...'),
('1105476', 'Felin Salsabila', 'AN ANALYSIS OF TRANSITIVITY SYSTEM IN STUDENTS'' ACADEMIC WRITING TEXTS (A Case Study of International Program on Science Education Students in a State University in Bandung)\r\n', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Emi Emilia, M.Ed.', 'Iyen Nurlaelawati, M.Pd.', 'This study entitled ''An Analysis of Transitivity System in Students'' Academic Writing Texts'' investigated how the students present scientific information in their academic writing seen from the Transitivity System, and what the difficulties are encountered by the students while writing their texts. This study is a qualitative study which was conducted in the English for Academic Purposes class in an International Program of Science Education in a state university in Bandung. The data were collected from the documents of six students'' writing texts from three different categories based on students'' achievement during their study. The texts were analyzed using Transitivity System proposed by Halliday (1994) and Eggins (2004); the theory of scientific texts suggested by Halliday & Martin (1993), Martin &Veel (1998), Fang (2005), and Fang (2006); and the theory of text types in science proposed by ...'),
('1105634', 'Juwita Purnama Sari', 'The Use of Photograph as A Visual Aid in Teaching Report Text Writing', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Fuad Abdul Hamied, M.A., Ph.D.', 'Rd. Della Nuridah Kartika Sari A., S.Pd., M.Ed.', 'This study was conducted to explore the use of photograph as a visual aid by the teacher in teaching report text writing. This study was a descriptive qualitative case study. The participants of this study were an English teacher as the main participant of this study and a ninth grade class of one of Junior High School in Bandung consisted of 35 students. The data were obtained from classroom observation and interview. The overall findings revealed the whole process of the use of photograph as a visual aid by the teacher from the consideration in designing the lesson plan, selecting the photographs, the findings in classroom observation and interview. Furthermore, this research also showed several findings, those are the use of photograph helps the teacher in delivering the material, the use of photograph can connect the students with their experience in their own environment, and for the stude...'),
('1105768', 'Farida', 'The Quality of EFL Students'' Participation in Genre Based Approach Implementation', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Didi Suherdi, M.Ed.', '', 'This study addresses an issue of the lack of students'' participation in classroom. The aim of the study is to describe the quality of students'' participation in GBA implementation since it emphasizes the critical importance of interaction and apprenticeship. A class consisted of 36 of nine graders were observed as the subjects of the study. Furthermore, to collect and identify the data, the study employed qualitative approach with descriptive method. In addition, Suherdi''s framework of classroom discourse analysis was used to analyze the data. Three elements of students'' participation were analyzed, including the quality of students-teacher interaction, the quality of students'' verbal linguistic and the quality of students'' learning behaviour. The study found out that the quality of students-teacher interaction is relatively high and interactive. On the other hand, the quality of students'' verb...'),
('1105773', 'Ahmad Abdan Sakuro', 'Classroom Discourse: Teacher-Student Interation Analysis', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Didi Suherdi, M.Ed.', '', 'This study entitled Classroom Discourse Analysis: Teacher-Student Interaction aims at finding the categories of exchanges in teacher talk and student talk used during interaction in English class as well as finding how the Teacher Talk (TT) is affecting the variation of classroom interaction patterns.The study employed a qualitative research design. The data were collected through videotape and questionnaire. The data were analyzed by applying framework of Categories of Exchanges proposed by Suherdi (2010) and Foreign Language Interaction System (FLINT). The findings of this study found many categories of exchanges in teacher talk and student talk. However, from those categories, the most dominant category which occurs in the teaching-learning session is simple non-anomalous K1-initiated category. Those categories are bound with the teacher''s performance during the teaching-learning session. Si...'),
('1106491', 'Mochammad Ircham Maulana', 'Reading Aloud and Silent Reading to EFL High School Students'' Reading Comprehension', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Nenden Sri Lengkanawati, M.Pd.', '', 'The present study entitled "Reading Aloud and Silent Reading Effects to Senior High School Students'' Reading Comprehension" aims to determine which mode of reading gives better effects to high school students'' reading comprehension. The equivocation of research related to which mode of reading gives better effect to senior high school students'' reading comprehension is the main reason why the present research was administered. Quantitative method with expost facto design was applied to look for the data. 80 11th grade students were involved in the research. They were assigned to answer 10 comprehension questions after reading 3 exposition texts with certain mode of reading. 40 students were asked to read the texts silently while the other 40 students were assigned to read aloud. The findings of the research revealed that silent reading mode gave better effects on the students'' reading comprehen...'),
('1106493', 'Desi Ristiani', 'Improving Students'' Ability in Writing Recount Text through Electronic Journaling', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Didi Suherdi, M.Ed.', 'Pupung Purnawarman, M.S.Ed., Ph.D.', 'This study was aimed at investigating the effectiveness of electronic journaling implementation to improve students'' writing ability especially in writing Recount Text and students'' responses toward the implementation of it. The study employed quasi-experimental design by using three instruments namely pretest, posttest, and questionnaire. Seventy two students of Grade VIII in a Junior High School in Bandung participated in the research. The data were analyzed by using SPSS 20 for Windows. The results reveal that there was a significant improvement on students'' writing in the experimental group after receiving treatment for six meetings, which means that electronic journaling was effective to improve students'' ability in writing Recount Text. Furthermore, the findings from questionnaire show that electronic journaling was positively accepted by most of the students. Finally, electronic journali...'),
('1106494', 'Ririen Riesty Riantini', 'The Identification of Teacher''s Questions in Genre Based Approach Implementation', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Didi Suherdi, M.Ed.', '', 'The paper entitled "The Identification of Teacher''s Questions in Genre Based Approach Implementation" aims to identify types of questions used by teacher by categorizing each type of questions according to Moore (2001). The purposes of the study are to identify the most dominant type of questions used by teacher in each stage of Genre Based Approach implementation and to discover how the type of questions influences students in learning. This study was conducted in EFL classroom for thirteen meetings which applied Genre base approach as the method of teaching and the topic was procedure text. The result of the study shows that factual questions were mostly used by the teacher in every stages of Genre Based Approach. Factual questions are questions used to lead students to recall information given. In teaching procedure text, these questions mostly used to ask structure, vocabularies and meaning...'),
('1206798', 'Chun Jinseo', 'A COMPARATIVE STUDY ON THE TEACHING METHOD OF ENGLISH GRAMMAR IN KOREA AND INDONESIA', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Pupung Purnawarman, M.S.Ed., Ph.D.', 'Muhammad Handi Gunawan, M.Pd.', 'This study is a comparative study on the teaching methods of English grammar in Korea and Indonesia as countries in EFL context. The study is aimed to Compare the current teaching methods of English grammar between South Korea and Indonesia and explore the effective grammar teaching methods in EFL context, considering the perception of the students and teachers. 30 junior high school teachers in Korea and 30 teachers and 90 students in junior high schools in Indonesia were involved as participants of the study. This study employed a qualitative method to compare teaching methods and explore teachers'' and students'' perception on the methods. The data collection was through questionnaires for teachers and students. '),
('0908974', 'Asep Saeful Anwar', 'EFEKTIVITAS PENGGUNAAN MEDIA KOMIK TERHADAP PENINGKATAN KEMAMPUAN DALAM MEMAHAMI KOSAKATA BAHASA ARAB (Studi Eksperimen Semu Terhadap Siswa kelas XI MAN 1 Bandung Tahun Ajaran 2012-2013)', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Arab', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr. Agus Salam Rahmat, M.Pd.', 'Drs. Ahmad Sukarna Firdaus, M.Pd.', 'Penelitian ini dilatarbelakangi oleh pengalaman peneliti dan banyaknya siswa yang mengalami kesulitan dalam menguasai kosakata bahasa Arab. Metode yang digunakan dalam penelitian ini adalah Kuasi-eksperimen, dengan desain Non-Equivalent Control Group Design. Dalam penelitian ini, peneliti memilih anggota kelompok eksperimen dan anggota kelompok kontrol masing-masing 30 orang di kelas XI MAN 1 Bandung tahun ajaran 2012/2013. Selanjutnya kelompok eksperimen dikenai perlakuan (treatment) yaitu media Komik, sementara kelompok kontrol tidak menerima perlakuan yang sama. Adapun pengujian hipotesis post-test kedua kelas tersebut. Setelah dilakukan uji Mann Whitney U-test dengan taraf signifikansi 0,05 diperoleh asymp. Sig (2-tailed) 0,00. Kriteria pengujian adalah H1 diterima jika < 0,05. Dengan demikian dapat dibuat keputusan H1 diterima dan H0 ditolak. Artinya disimpulkan bahwa penggunaan media Komi...'),
('1005464', 'Balebat Kania Sari', 'Pengaruh Persepsi Siswa tentang Bahasa Arab terhadap Proses Belajar Bahasa Arab Siswa (Studi Korelasi terhadap Siswa Kelas XI PGII 1 Bandung Tahun Ajaran 2013/2014)', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Arab', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr.  Rahmat Hidayat, M.Pd.', 'Mohamad Zaka Al Farisi, S.Pd., M.Hum.', 'Penelitian ini didasari oleh asumsi setiap individu (siswa) yang mempunyai persepsi tertentu mengenai suatu objek, khususnya bahasa Arab. Dengan dilatarbelakangi oleh faktor yang menuntut siswa mempelajari bahasa Arab, maka proses belajar bahasa Arab siswa pun beragam. Maka terdapat kemungkinan bahwa dari persepsi siswa akan menghasilkan proses belajar yang berbeda. Adapun tujuan penelitian ini yaitu untuk menemukan ada atau tidak ada pengaruh yang signifikan antara persepsi siswa tentang bahasa Arab terhadap proses belajar bahasa Arab siswa. Penelitian ini menggunakan metode penelitian korelasional yang termasuk dalam penelitian kuantitatif non eksperimental serta menggunakan desain penelitian kausal. Sampel diambil menggunakan teknik quota sampling dan snowball sampling yang termasuk dalam teknik nonprobability sampling. Hasil dari penelitian menunjukkan persepsi siswa tentang bahasa Arab ter...'),
('1100739', 'Reni Safitri', 'Analisis Kesalahan Fonologis dalam Bacaan Surah Al Fatihah (Studi Deskriptif Terhadap Kesalahan Fonologis pada Suku-Suku  Indonesia dalam Membaca Surah Al Fatihah)', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Arab', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr. Agus Salam Rahmat, M.Pd.', 'Mohamad Zaka Al Farisi, S.Pd., M.Hum.', 'Pengalaman peneliti ketika bertemu dengan masyarakat dari berbagai suku di lingkungan Universitas Pendidikan Indonesia membuktikan adanya permasalahan dalam membaca al-Qur''an dimana ketika mahasiswa melakukan tes dengan UKM BAQI harus mengulang tes berkali-kali untuk mendapatkan kategori lulus dan mendapatkan nilai TT (Tingkat Terampil). Hal inilah yang menarik perhatian peneliti untuk mengkaji kesalahan-kesalahan fonologis yang dilakukan oleh masyarakat dari berbagai suku di lingkungan sekitar UPI. Berkenaan dengan hal ini terdapat tiga tujuan yaitu untuk mengetahui kesalahan apa saja yang dilakukan orang Indonesia dalam membaca surah al-Fatihah, untuk mengetahui faktor-faktor yang menyebabkan kesalahan dalam membaca surah al-Fatihah, dan untuk mengetahui usaha yang dilakukan orang Indonesia untuk mengurangi kesalahan dalam membaca surah al-Fatihah. Teknik pengumpulan data yang dilakukan penel...'),
('1100758', 'Egi Zaelani', 'EFEKTIFITAS METODE CONTEXTUAL TEACHING AND LEARNING (CTL) TERHADAP KEMAMPUAN BERBICARA BAHASA ARAB ', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Arab', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr. Maman Abdurahman, M.Ag.', 'Dr. Madali, M.A.', 'Efektifitas metode pembelajaran kontekstual terhadap kemampuan berbicara bahasa arab (studi experimen kuasi siswa Kelas XI SMA PGII 1 Bandung Tahun Ajaran 2015/2016). Kemampuan berbicara merupakan kemampuan yang sangat penting dalam mempelajari bahasa Arab, karena secara umum kemampuan berbicara bertujuan agar peserta didik mampu berkomunikasi lisan secara baik dan benar, Namun kenyataannya kemampuan berbicara bahasa Arab siswa PGII 1 Bandung masih rendah, padahal kemampuan berbicara bahasa Arab sangat diperlukan. Maka dari itu peneliti menggunakan metode pembelajaran kontekstual dalam memudahkan siswa belajar berbicara bahasa Arab. Metode yang digunakan dalam penelitian ini adalah metode quasi eksperimental nonequivalent control group design. Hasil analisis data yang dilakukan di SMA PGII 1 Bandung, peneliti menemukan bahwa kemampuan berbicara bahasa Arab siswa kurang dari yang diharapkan. Unt...'),
('1101784', 'Fahmi Ahmad Huwaidi ', 'STUDI SEMANTIK UNGKAPAN INSYA ALLAH DALAM AL-QURAN (Analisis Leksikal, Gramatikal dan Kontekstual Ungkapan insya Allah serta Pemahamannya di Masyarakat)', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Arab', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Syihabuddin, M.Pd.', 'Dr. Dedeng Rosyidin, M.Pd.', 'STUDI SEMANTIK UNGKAPAN INSYA ALLAH DALAM AL QURAN. Penelitian ini bertujuan untuk menjelaskan hakikat makna ungkapan insya Allah dalam al Quran. Hal ini dikarenakan ungkapan Insya Allah sering kali diartikan dengan makna yang keliru oleh masyarakat Indonesia sehingga berdampak kepada sebagian masyarakat menggunakan ungkapan tersebut dalam keadaan yang keliru. Penelitian ini menggunakan metode deskriptif dengan pendekatan kualitatif. Subjek penelitian ini adalah ungkapan insya Allah pada ayat-ayat al Quran dan ungkapan keseharian yang digunakan oleh masyarakat Indonesia. Metode pengumpulan data menggunakan observasi, wawancara terstruktur, dan dokumentasi. Hasil penelitian mengungkapkan bahwa ungkapan Insya Allah dalam al Quran memiliki makna semoga Allah menghendaki yang disertai tekad kuat dalam diri untuk menunaikan janji. Sedangkan ungkapan yang digunakan masyarakat memiliki makna yang bera...'),
('1101821', 'Muhammad Reza', 'EFEKTIVITAS PENDEKATAN KOMUNIKATIF DALAM MENINGKATKAN HASIL BELAJAR BAHASA ARAB SISWA (Studi Eksperimen Kuasi Melalui PAKEM di MTs.S Ar-Rohmah Sukajadi Bandung)', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Arab', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Dr. Ahmad Suherman, M.Pd.', 'Dr.  Rahmat Hidayat, M.Pd.', 'EFEKTIVITAS PENDEKATAN KOMUNIKATIF DALAM MENINGKATKAN HASIL BELAJAR BAHASA ARAB SISWA (Studi Eksperimen Kuasi Melalui PAKEM di MTSS. Ar-Rohmah Sukajadi Bandung). Penelitian ini dilatar belakangi oleh kondisi siswa yang sulit untuk aktif mengekporasi pembelajaran bahasa Arab dan senantiasa mengandalkan materi yang diberikan oleh guru saja, sehingga kurang terjadi umpan balik dari siswa kepada guru atau dalam artian pembelajaran berjalan satu arah (tidak komunikatf). Keaktifan siswa dalam mengekplorasi pembelajaran merupakan faktor yang mempengaruhi pemahaman siswa akan pembelajaran bahasa asing, jika siswa memiliki pemahaman yang baik dan mampu mengembangkannya maka ini akan dapat meningkatkan hasil belajar yang di peroleh siswa. Oleh karena itu, penulis menganggap penting untuk meneliti permasalahan yang ditemukan di lapangan tersebut dan sebagai solusinya penulis mencoba menggunakan pendekatan...'),
('1102032', 'Mia Nurmala', 'Penggunaan Mashdar dalam Al-Quran Juz Satu dan Implikasinya terhadap Pembelajaran Tarjamah', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Arab', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Syihabuddin, M.Pd.', 'Asep Sopian, S.Pd., M.Ag.', 'Penelitian ini berangkat dari fenomena kesalahan penggunaan shighat dalam menerjemahkan serta pentingnya mengetahui macam-macam  dan penerjemahan mashdar ke dalam bahasa Indonesia karena merupakan shighat yang memiliki fungsi beragam dalam penggunaannya. Penelitian ini bertujuan untuk mengetahui dan memahami jenis dan teknik penerjemahan ke dalam bahasa Indonesia mashdar dalam  juz satu, serta implikasinya terhadap pembelajaran Tarjamah. Adapun pendekatan yang digunakan dalam penelitian ini adalah studi literatur. Pola penelitian yang digunakan adalah analisis deskriptif. Sedangkan sumber rujukan berupa buku sebagai penunjang adalah kitab-kitab Tafsir, Nahwu, dan Sharaf. Dengan itu, peneliti mengklasifikasikan mashdar berdasarkan pada dua kategori; Pertama, berdasarkan pada bentuknya terbagi dua bagian, yaitu mashdar sharih dan mashdar muawwal, mashdar sharih disebut sebanyak 234 kali dan mashd...'),
('1102335', 'Mira Nurpratiwi', 'Pengaruh Media Pembelajaran Hadiqatulhuruf terhadap Peningkatan Kemampuan Menulis Kata Bahasa Arab (Studi Eksperimen Kuasi pada Siswa Kelas VII SMP Miftahul Iman Bandung Tahun Ajaran 2014-2015)', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Arab', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'DR. YAYAN NURBAYAN, M.AG.', 'Dr. Nunung Nursyamsiah, M.Pd.', 'Pengaruh media Hadiqatulhuruf terhadap kemampuan menulis kata bahasa Arab. Penelitian ini dilatarbelakangi oleh minimnya kemampuan siswa dalam menulis huruf Arab yang menyebabkan siswa kesulitan mengisi lembar jawaban ujian. Selain itu, media yang digunakan dalam pembelajaran juga kurang beragam. Dalam penelitian ini, peneliti menggunakan media Hadiqatulhuruf untuk membantu mengatasi permaslahan yang dialami oleh siswa kelas VII di SMP Miftahul Iman Bandung. Dengan penggunaan media Hadiqatulhuruf ini diharapkan akan menjadi salah satu cara untuk membantu siswa mengatasi permaslahan yang mereka alami. Penelitian ini menggunakan pendekatan kuantitatif  dengan metode studi eksperimen kuasi desain non-equivalent control group. Dalam penelitian ini, sample penelitian yaitu kelas VII B sebagai kelas eksperimen dan kelas VII A sebagai kelas kontrol. Setelah dilakukan pembelajaran dengan menggunakan me...'),
('1102442', 'Abdul Rahman Sidiq', 'Efektivitas Penggunaan Media Kartu Uno Terhadap Peningkatan Kemampuan Menerjemah Kalimat Sederhana Bahasa Arab (Studi Eksperimen kuasi terhadap siswa kelas VII SMP Plus Babussalam Ciburial Tahun Ajaran 2015-2016)', 'Pendidikan Bahasa Arab', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'DR. YAYAN NURBAYAN, M.AG.', 'Dr. Dedeng Rosyidin, M.Pd.', 'Efektivitas Penggunaan Media Kartu Uno Terhadap Peningkatan Kemampuan Menerjemah Kalimat Sederhana Bahasa Arab. Media permainan kartu Uno merupakan salah satu media yang dapat dijadikan sebagai media pembelajaran dalam menerjemah dan memperkaya perbendaharan kosakata karena karakteristik dari kartu Uno sudah populer di Indonesia. Bentuk dan desain dari kartu Uno yang sederhana dan juga mudah untuk disesuaikan dengan kebutuhan dari penulis. Lokasi penelitian ini adalah SMP Plus Babussalam Jalan Ciburial Indah 5 desa Ciburial kecamatan Cimenyan Kabupaten Bandung. Populasi dalam penelitian ini adalah seluruh siswa kelas VII SMP Plus Babus Salam Kabupaten Bandung tahun ajaran 2015/2016. Adapun tujuan penelitian ini adalah mengetahui kemampuan siswa dalam memahami terjemah bahasa Arab sebelum penerapan permainan kartu Uno, mengetahui kemampuan siswa dalam memahami terjemah bahasa Arab setelah setela...');
