('1000649', 'Fadhlillah Sariwibawa Ahmad Zaeni', 'The Representation of Mount Slamet Disaster in the Online Media of Tempo and Time', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Iwa Lukmana, M.A., Ph.D.', '', 'The study examines the representation of Mount Slamet disaster in online media in Tempo and Time. It mainly employs a descriptive qualitative method. The data include twelve articles from Tempo and one article from Time related to the volcanic activity. The analysis employs the framework of socio-cognitive approach, including macrostructure and microstructure analyses. Halliday''s transitivity is used in microstructure analysis to examine the representation of experiences in the articles. The macrostructure analysis discloses three findings, namely the topics discussed in relation to the disaster, the quotation strategy, and the use of sources. Tempo and Time have a similarity of quotation strategy despite having differences in terms of variation of topics and the sources used in the articles. The microstructure analysis reveals that Tempo and Time represented the disaster mostly in material and...'),
