('1002594', 'Kinanti Adyawardhani', 'The Representation Of Consumptive Lifestyle In Selected Instagram Photos', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Prof. Dr. Didi Sukyadi, M.A.', 'Budi Hermawan, S.Pd., M.PC.', 'The present study is mainly conducted to investigate how lifestyle is represented in selected Instagram photos. The study is also aimed at finding out the interaction established between the verbal and the visual modes in selected Instagram photos. The study applies descriptive qualitative study and employs multimodal analysis to answer the research questions. The data were analyzed using Martinec and Salway''s text-image relation system (2005), Halliday''s transitivity system (Gerott & Wignell, 1994), and Kress and van Leeuwen''s Reading Images (2006). The findings show that 1) the verbal and visual modes in selected Instagram photos mostly interact through unequal status in which one of them is mostly related as the additional information for the other mode and the realization or example of the other mode; 2) lifestyle may be used as the identity of Instagram users. In this context, the lifestyl...'),
('1002638', 'Alif Fauziyyah', 'REVEALING THE TRANSLATOR''S MAGIC: A STUDY OF THE TRANSLATOR''S VOICE IN CASSANDRA CLARE''S CITY OF BONES', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Drs. Ahsin Mohamad, M.Ag.', 'Susi Septaviana R., M.Pd.', 'The study investigates the cases of translator''s voice occurred in the Indonesian version of Cassandra Clare''s City of Bones. The study is framed within the theory of translator''s voice proposed by Hermans (2010). The study employs a qualitative method and content analysis to analyze the data. The result of the study shows that all three cases (Text''s Orientation Towards an Implied Reader, Self-reflexiveness and Self-referentiality, and Contextual Overdetermination) are occurred in the translated text with the case of Self-reflexiveness and Self-referentiality as the most frequent case, with 170 occurrences from the total number of all cases which is 196 occurrences. It signified translator''s attempt to intervene the author''s voice in the translation in order to be able to deliver the message smoothly. In addition, idiom is the feature from the case that showed up the most. The case occur in th...'),
