('1006115', 'Wildhan Akbar Kusumah', 'Ideology Construction and Its Signification (A Socio-Cognitive Analysis of the Selected Bob Marley''s Lyrics)', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Ahmad Bukhori Muslim, S.Pd., M.Ed.', '', 'This paper entitled Ideology Construction and Its Signification A Socio-Cognitive Analysis of the Selected Bob Marley''s Song lyrics aims to uncover the ideology constructed within Bob Marley''s selected lyrics and its signification. This study uses a qualitative descriptive method. Van Dijk''s (2009) Socio-Cognitive Approach is utilized as framework in this study. The results of this study show that Rastafari ideology is constructed within the analyzed lyrics. It is identified through the occurrence of its value within the topic selection which is supported by the use of metaphor and narrator shifting. The occurrence of ideology within the lyric indicates the ideology the writer brings is based on the awareness of social problem, especially social injustice issue.'),
('1006231', 'Dobes Martin Turnip', 'An Analysis of Translation Procedures of Cultural Words in Harper Lee''s To Kill A Mockingbird', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Isti Siti Saleha Gandana, M.Ed., Ph.D.', 'Susi Septaviana R., M.Pd.', 'Translation procedures have become an important issue in the translation process. Translation procedures are procedures used to translate smaller units of language, such as sentences, phrases, and words. This research study is entitled An Analysis of Translation Procedures of Cultural Words in Harper Lee''s To Kill a Mockingbird. This study aimed to identify the cultural words categories based on Nedergaard-Larsen''s theory of cultural categories (1993, in Kyla-Harakka, 2008). This research study also intended to identify the translation procedures used by the translator in translating the identified cultural words in the novel by using translation procedures proposed by Molina and Albir (2002). To answer the research questions, this research study used descriptive qualitative method. The findings show that society (44%) is the cultural words category that frequently appeared, followed by culture...'),
