('1006352', 'Nanda Satia Nugraha', '', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', '', '', 'This present study aims to discover the heroic journey of one Watchmen''s character, Ozymandias, and how focalization of that character occurs in the film. The study uses the 12 stages of heroic journey model as the theoretical framework proposed by Vogler (2007), along with the theory of focalization based on the concept of focalization in film narratology by Verstraten (2009). The data collected are taken from the film''s scenes in which Ozymandias appear and related evidences in form of film snapshots. This study finds that Ozymandias has a unique heroic journey, which mainly follows Vogler''s 12 stages of heroic journey, with additional stage that deviates his heroic journey from getting completed.\r\nKeywords: Heroic Journey, Narratology, Focalization,\r\n'),
('1006451', 'Mohammad Fatih Zahid ', 'Idiomatic Expressions Translation Analyisis In Arthur Golden''s Novel Memoirs Of A Geisha', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Drs. Ahsin Mohamad, M.Ag.', 'Susi Septaviana R., M.Pd.', 'The study aims to identify the types of idioms, find out the strategies used by the translator, and investigate the degree of equivalent meaning of idiomatic expressions found in the novel Memoirs of a Geisha. The data were taken from 150 idioms found in the novel. The data were then analyzed by using the types of idioms proposed by Lim (2004). After that, the researcher investigated which strategies were used by the translator in translating idioms proposed by Baker (1992) and then the researcher investigated the degree of equivalent meaning of each idiom and its translation by using a theory proposed by Bell (1991). The results showed that Phrasal verbs are the most frequent type of idioms found in the novel with the percentages of 49% of the whole data. For the strategy used by the translator, the study showed that translation by paraphrase is the most frequent strategy used by the translato...'),
('1006676', 'Indry Caesarria Dewi', 'Audiovisual Translation Of English Idioms In Harry Potter And The Deathly Hallows Movie: An Analysis Of English to Indonesian Subtitle', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Drs. Ahsin Mohamad, M.Ag.', 'Susi Septaviana R., M.Pd.', 'The research entitled Audiovisual Translation of English Idioms in Harry Potter and The Deathly Hallows Movie : An Analysis of English to Indonesian Subtitle aims at discovering types of idioms which are mostly used in the movie and analyzing the translation strategies dealing with the idioms in the movie. The data were analyzed by using a descriptive qualitative method with Fernando''s (1996) typology of idioms and Gottlieb''s (1992) strategies for the translation process of subtitling. The result of data analysis shows that pure idiom has the largest number of the total idiom found in the movie, that is 50 items (50%). The second finding shows that the most frequent strategies used by the translator is paraphrase which is used 41 times or reaches 41% of the total usage. Subsequently, strategies which less frequent in a row are transfer (40%), expansion (9%), condensation (4%), deletion (3%), an...'),
