('1100089', 'Intan Aulia Istiqomah', 'The Representation of Bali Nine Execution Case in The Jakarta Post and The ABC', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Eri Kurniawan, S.Pd., M.A., Ph.D.', 'DIAN YULIANA, M.PD.', 'This study investigates the representation of Bali Nine Execution Case in The Jakarta Post and The ABC by employing ideological square which is proposed by Van Dijk (2000). The analysis focuses on two semantic macro-strategies of positive self-presentation and negative other-presentation which are realized through the use of discursive strategies. Two articles from each newspaper become the sample of analysis to conduct the study. The findings show that The ABC and The Jakarta Post represent the same issue differently. The use of discursive strategies plays fundamental role in the representation of Bali Nine Execution Case. In representing the issue, The ABC uses a lot of discursive strategies to form the positive self-presentation and negative other-presentation. On the other hand, only several discursive strategies are found in The Jakarta Post''s articles. Moreover, The Jakarta Post only crea...'),
('1100103', 'Abdurrahman Karim', 'The Analysis Of Amateur Subtitling Of Comic 8 From A Multimodal Perspective', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Isti Siti Saleha Gandana, M.Ed., Ph.D.', 'Susi Septaviana R., M.Pd.', 'The present research provides an analysis of amateur subtitling of Comic 8, an Indonesian action-comedy movie, from a multimodal perspective. It aims at finding out the collaboration of subtitles and moving images in conveying the meanings in the scenes, as well as the issues found in the analysis which are related to the practice of amateur subtitling. The collaboration of the subtitles and the non-verbal modes in the scenes can be observed from the relationship between verbal elements (dialogue and subtitles) and non-verbal elements (moving images and sound) in the film, referring to Barthes'' concept on text-image relationship (1977, in Kress & van Leeuwen, 2006) and the concept of redundancy proposed by Marleau (1982, in D?az-Cintas & Remael, 2014). Based on the analysis, it is found that the non-verbal modes mainly function to illustrate the situation in the scene, while the subtitles mainl...'),
('1100388', 'Ani Rahmaeni', '', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', '', '', 'This research aims to investigate verbal texts in Pantene TV Commercials that were advertised in two culturally different markets, Indonesia and USA. This research is looking at the occurrences of mood types, modality and also the use of personal pronouns in order to realize the characteristics of audiences who have different culture. The data were taken from Pantene Indonesia website on Facebook for PI (Pantene Indonesia) and Pantene website on Youtube for PU (Pantene USA). The framework of Gerot and Wignell''s (1994) theory of Mood Types is adopted. The findings show that there are different characteristics between PI and PU audiences in which PI audiences prefer assertive and direct advertisements, while PU audiences prefer persuasive and indirect advertisements. Thus, culture unconsciously determines the audiences'' characteristics.\r\nKeywords: Advertisements, Verbal Text, Interpersonal Meanin...'),
('1100547', 'Ahmad Meizar Rashyd', '', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', '', '', ''),
('1100678', 'Fadhilla Azhimi', 'An Analysis Of Turn-Taking Rules In A TV Program "Ini Talk Show"', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Eri Kurniawan, S.Pd., M.A., Ph.D.', '', 'This research investigates the use of turn-taking rules in the talk show Ini Talk Show. The approach employed in this research is Conversation Analysis (CA) proposed by Sacks, Schegloff, and Jefferson (1974). By adapting a descriptive qualitative method, this study examines one of the episodes in the talk show Ini Talk Showentitled "96.7 Hits FM". The focus of this study is the conversations among seven speakers, including two hosts and fiveguests, of the talk show. It is to determine the use of turn-taking rules in the conversations and to discover the factors that influence the use of the rules. The results show that the rule which is mostly used in the conversation is Current Speaker Selects the Next Speaker (CS2TNS) rule, and power relation factor influences the use of turn-taking rules in the conversation of the talk show. Thus, it can be said that the one who takes control in the conversa...'),
('1101007', 'Rendy Renaldy', 'The Discursive Construction of KPK (Corruption Eradication Commission) and Polri (Indonesian National Police) in the Jakarta Post: a Discourse-Historical Approach', 'Bahasa dan Sastra Inggris', 'FAKULTAS PENDIDIKAN BAHASA DAN SASTRA', 'Ahmad Bukhori Muslim, S.Pd., M.Ed.', '', 'This study investigates discursive construction employed by the Jakarta Post in the news of KPK and Polri through nomination and predication strategies of Discourse-Historical Approach (DHA) proposed by Reisigl and Wodak (2001). KPK (Corruption Eradication Commission) is a government agency established to fight corruption, meanwhile Polri is Indonesian National Police. This study uses descriptive qualitative method to analyze five news articles about KPK and Polri. The aim of the study is to identify how social actors in the related news articles are referred to and predicated by the Jakarta Post. The findings reveal two main points. First, proper name is the most frequent linguistic device in nomination strategies used by the Jakarta Post in referring to social actors of KPK and Polri issues. Second, explicit predicate is the most frequent predication strategies employed by the Jakarta Post in...'),
